I'm curious too.

00:36:01.530 --> 00:36:06.610
What was it like to describe
yourself as a paradox, or to

00:36:06.610 --> 00:36:08.830
dip down beneath the surface?

00:36:08.830 --> 00:36:12.500
Did anyone feel some real
connection and intimacy with

00:36:12.500 --> 00:36:15.090
this other person that was
a little surprising?

00:36:15.090 --> 00:36:20.255
Right here in the middle
of a Google-y Monday?

00:36:20.255 --> 00:36:22.610
[INAUDIBLE]

00:36:22.610 --> 00:36:27.990
So you, so your comment was
you were surprised at the

00:36:27.990 --> 00:36:32.850
commonality of the way your
partner described herself or

00:36:32.850 --> 00:36:34.270
himself as a paradox.

00:36:34.270 --> 00:36:38.110
And you always thought
it was just you.

00:36:38.110 --> 00:36:40.405
I've noticed that whole--

00:36:43.530 --> 00:36:45.870
it's one of the really wonderful
things about having

00:36:45.870 --> 00:36:47.960
real conversations
with people.

00:36:47.960 --> 00:36:50.210
So that would be--

00:36:50.210 --> 00:36:52.300
One of things that I talk
about in the book is

00:36:52.300 --> 00:36:55.630
recommending a personal audit.

00:36:55.630 --> 00:37:03.580
Actually, so it's one thing to
say start where you are or

00:37:03.580 --> 00:37:04.670
accepting what is.

00:37:04.670 --> 00:37:07.370
But it's interesting actually
to start with

00:37:07.370 --> 00:37:09.580
what actually is.

00:37:09.580 --> 00:37:13.000
And one of the-- there's what
I think of as the things we

00:37:13.000 --> 00:37:15.340
all know and maybe some of us
do or don't do, which is

00:37:15.340 --> 00:37:17.940
things like getting
enough sleep,

00:37:17.940 --> 00:37:21.080
exercise, eating good food.

00:37:21.080 --> 00:37:24.210
But I think the kind of food
that I think may be one of the

00:37:24.210 --> 00:37:28.817
most important foods is our
relationships, and the level

00:37:28.817 --> 00:37:32.740
of openness and intimacy
in our relationships.

00:37:32.740 --> 00:37:35.010
So one of the things you might
do in a personal audit is

00:37:35.010 --> 00:37:38.440
start to keep track of how many
real conversations do you

00:37:38.440 --> 00:37:41.620
have with someone
during the day.

00:37:41.620 --> 00:37:43.140
Just notice.

00:37:43.140 --> 00:37:46.250
And you can define a real
conversation maybe as where

00:37:46.250 --> 00:37:51.300
you or someone else actually
expressed some emotion, and

00:37:51.300 --> 00:37:52.680
there might have been
some emotional

00:37:52.680 --> 00:37:55.110
connection with people.

00:37:55.110 --> 00:37:58.880
And just start to, just maybe
for a week, start to jot down

00:37:58.880 --> 00:38:02.370
at the end of each day how many
real conversations, how

00:38:02.370 --> 00:38:06.600
many intimate conversations
did I have during the day.

00:38:06.600 --> 00:38:09.300
For some people, I think--

00:38:09.300 --> 00:38:13.230
it's interesting this is
partly a gender thing.

00:38:13.230 --> 00:38:18.120
I think women tend to talk a lot
more about their feelings

00:38:18.120 --> 00:38:22.430
and emotions, and men tend to
talk a lot less about feelings

00:38:22.430 --> 00:38:23.050
and emotions.

00:38:23.050 --> 00:38:27.710
That's just a generalization
which isn't 100 percent true.

00:38:27.710 --> 00:38:30.560
But wherever you are, man or
woman, just notice where are

00:38:30.560 --> 00:38:37.640
you on that scale, and how
might it be beneficial to

00:38:37.640 --> 00:38:41.660
shift that needle in terms of
having the right amount of

00:38:41.660 --> 00:38:45.986
intimate, real conversations
during your day.

