00:38:51.974 --> 00:38:53.371
white-- this is the right thing
to do; this is the wrong

00:38:53.371 --> 00:38:54.469
thing to do.

00:38:54.469 --> 00:38:55.966
This is the right thing,
I have to do

00:38:55.966 --> 00:38:57.463
to climb the ladder.

00:38:57.463 --> 00:38:58.960
What do you recommend?

00:38:58.960 --> 00:38:59.958
How can we--

00:38:59.958 --> 00:39:02.952
what are the pieces we can
contribute for people to

00:39:02.952 --> 00:39:07.530
embrace the gray area and the
growth and the tension in our

00:39:07.530 --> 00:39:09.860
day-to-day [INAUDIBLE]

00:39:09.860 --> 00:39:10.250
MARC LESSER: Yeah.

00:39:10.250 --> 00:39:13.950
Well I think, especially in this
kind of environment and

00:39:13.950 --> 00:39:17.860
in a lot of business
environments, we want things

00:39:17.860 --> 00:39:18.850
to be clear.

00:39:18.850 --> 00:39:19.040
Right?

00:39:19.040 --> 00:39:20.230
We want clarity.

00:39:20.230 --> 00:39:21.760
We want that sense of ladder.

00:39:21.760 --> 00:39:27.060
And I think we should spend as
much time as it takes to get

00:39:27.060 --> 00:39:28.350
that clear.

00:39:28.350 --> 00:39:33.140
But I think to be successful,
to really be successful and

00:39:33.140 --> 00:39:37.250
happy, both in this environment
or pretty much any

00:39:37.250 --> 00:39:41.345
environment, it's about
resilience and how we adapt.

00:39:44.610 --> 00:39:47.230
The business model here
for, there's so much

00:39:47.230 --> 00:39:48.700
change right here.

00:39:48.700 --> 00:39:53.508
It's announced Google
Reader, gone.

