This might be a sore point.

00:39:58.670 --> 00:40:01.580
I miss Google Reader,
but I get it, right?

00:40:01.580 --> 00:40:08.030
Because in my own company, you
have to make decisions.

00:40:08.030 --> 00:40:12.600
And not everyone's going to be--
it's hard being a leader.

00:40:12.600 --> 00:40:14.420
It's hard being a manager.

00:40:14.420 --> 00:40:19.100
You see as clearly as you can,
and then you know that there's

00:40:19.100 --> 00:40:20.890
a lot of things you
don't know.

00:40:20.890 --> 00:40:24.030
Who knew what would happen when
you make an announcement

00:40:24.030 --> 00:40:24.900
about Google Reader.

00:40:24.900 --> 00:40:26.310
Who knew?

00:40:26.310 --> 00:40:29.660
Or who knew when Netflix
announced that they were

00:40:29.660 --> 00:40:32.390
changing their whole
pricing scheme?

00:40:32.390 --> 00:40:37.460
And I think we're constantly,
whether it's out there

00:40:37.460 --> 00:40:41.930
experimenting with products and
services, and within our

00:40:41.930 --> 00:40:46.420
team, we're constantly, I think,
trying to get more

00:40:46.420 --> 00:40:52.380
understanding of who are these
other people on the team?

00:40:52.380 --> 00:40:55.080
One of the things we teach in
Search Inside Yourself is a

00:40:55.080 --> 00:40:56.990
political awareness.

00:40:56.990 --> 00:40:59.540
How does power work?

00:40:59.540 --> 00:41:01.960
How does power and decision
making work in this

00:41:01.960 --> 00:41:03.140
organization?

00:41:03.140 --> 00:41:05.900
And it's often pretty complex
and not so clear, so to be

00:41:05.900 --> 00:41:11.070
able to have a sense of clarity
and at the same time

00:41:11.070 --> 00:41:13.960
to be adaptive and resilient.

00:41:13.960 --> 00:41:18.280
And that also means being
willing to look stupid.

00:41:18.280 --> 00:41:20.080
Being willing to fail.

00:41:20.080 --> 00:41:20.230
All right.

00:41:20.230 --> 00:41:22.520
So I think, again this is
one of those paradoxes.

00:41:22.520 --> 00:41:25.440
The more we hold
on, the more--

00:41:25.440 --> 00:41:28.960
So it's a little bit like, as I
was describing my drive down

00:41:28.960 --> 00:41:30.740
